v 31 May 2016
Student Guide
The student guide attempts to satisfy the needs of several types of users. 
Students will need to refer to both this student guide and the Land SAR 
Addendum to the National SAR Supplement during class. The student 
guide is a training aid, assembling information and handouts for student
use and reference during classroom work, and provides information not 
found in the Land SAR Addendum or other resources available in the 
classroom. The information it contains does not supersede official policy 
or basic references such as the National Search and Rescue Supplement to 
the IAMSAR Manual and its addendums, and is only as accurate as the 
student’s ability to take accurate notes. The student guide has notes pages 
throughout to help students capture their ideas and plan actions they need 
to take after the course to improve their SAR response.
The student guide and provided course CD and Supplemental Readings 
contain copyrighted works reproduced with the permissions of the authors 
and/or original publishers. Each individual work is the property of its 
author and/or publisher and does not necessarily reflect the views or 
positions of the National SAR School or the US Air Force. Copyrights to 
each work are retained by the authors and/or publishers. In accordance 
with pertinent copyright laws, there may be no further reproduction or 
other use of the copyrighted materials contained in this volume without 
prior written permission from the authors and/or publishers.
