Inland SAR Planning Student Guide
52 30 October 2014
Lesson 6
INTRODUCTION TO SEARCH THEORY
The search planner’s challenge is determining how to most effectively use
available search assets to find the search object in the minimum time. 
However, the allocation of searchers to yield optimum results is not 
intuitive. This lesson is an introduction to search theory intended to
prepare you for more detailed materials in following lessons. As you read, 
recognize the lesson (and course) present search theory for planners, not 
for searchers. The planner’s job is to craft the best possible search plan 
with the greatest likelihood of finding the search object. The searchers 
execute the plan. 
After completing this lesson, students should:
• UNDERSTAND how a relatively small amount of mathematics can 
provide a large amount of assistance in the on-going planning of a 
search,
• RECOGNIZE the value of combining experience with mathematics,
