Mathematically Modeling SAR Resources
You are notified of a missing aircraft with an intended route of flight of 
220 nm. Use NASA World Wind SAR Visualization data to develop
search area: 10 nm extensions before LKP and after destination, and 
searching out to 10 nm offset left and right of intended route. 
Calculate how much area can be searched in one search period:
1. Determine the size of the desired search area (in nm2):
𝐴𝑟𝑒𝑎 (𝐴) = 𝑙𝑒𝑛𝑔𝑡ℎ 𝑥 𝑤𝑖𝑑𝑡ℎ
= (220𝑛𝑚 + 20𝑛𝑚) 𝑥 20𝑛𝑚 = 4800𝑛𝑚2
