Step Action
2f Each participant divides individual option numbers by his/her total:
Down Up Left Right Total
Rick .476 .357 .119 .048 1.000
Dan .588 .294 .088 .030 1.000
Mark .385 .513 .051 .051 1.000
A good check is to add up the decimals: they should equal 1.000. If they don’t you should 
adjust the rounding somewhat. In this case, Dan’s “right” figure was adjusted up from 
.0294 to .030 in order to ensure 100% of the probability was accounted for.
3-4 Sum the inputs for each scenario and divide by the number of participants:
