AMDR does have some immediate advantages. AMDR is measured onscene under actual search conditions (terrain, vegetation, weather) --- and 
typically by the actual searchers. Additionally, the measurement process 
is quick and easy to set up and does not require difficult mathematical 
computations. Finally, the concept of AMDR can be applied to nearly any 
search resource, including aircraft.
