Developing POD
This detection profile depicts the relationship between Coverage (C) and 
the average POD over an area for visual searches using parallel sweeps. 
We advise use of the more conservative exponential range curve (normal 
search conditions) rather than the inverse cube range curve (ideal search 
conditions).
Use of the POD vs. Coverage graph assumes that the entire search 
segment(s) be searched nearly uniformly, essentially equally well, across 
its entire extent without a great deal of overlapping from searchers 
crossing and re-crossing their paths or leaving portions uncovered.
Sometimes it is useful to know what it will take to achieve a desired result; 
in this case, the track spacing that must be accepted to achieve a desired 
POD. For a 1 square mile segment, searcher sweep width (W) is 100ft, 
searcher speed is 0.29 mph, and time in the search area is 5 hours. If the 
planners desire an 80% POD, what is the number of required searchers?
