In the equation; 
• “W” is Effective Sweep Width, 
• “v” is the average search speed, 
• “POC” is Probability of Containment, and
• “A” is the segment’s physical area.
Note the “before” subscripts in the PSR equation above indicate that the 
values describe the situation just prior to the segment being searched. 
After the segment is searched and the POC is adjusted for searching, the 
PSR, like POC, will be reduced. The equation for PSRafter remains the 
same except for the subscripts:
