Optimal Allocation
As discussed above in the section on PSR, once PSR is calculated for each 
and every segment in the search area, the segments can be rank-ordered 
from highest-to-lowest PSR and searchers can be assigned.
The “PSR Based Ground Effort Allocation Worksheet” you have 
completed guides the search planner through the rank order process and
allows experimentation to determine the benefits of any desired allocation 
of searchers into the field. Search planners must make their own decisions 
remembering that the mathematics does not capture all the operationally 
significant aspects of a search.
Search the segment again or expand into new segments? The “PSR Based 
Ground Effort Allocation Worksheet” can help you answer that question: 
when PSR of the searched segments are reduced to the PSR of an 
unsearched segment, add the new segment to the active search.
For examining the relative benefits of searching various segments within 
the search area, the basis of comparison is Probable Success Rate: the 
instantaneous rate of increase in POS for adding an additional resource.
