Optimal Allocation 
The highest POS is achieved when the after-search PSR of all segments 
searched are equal and not less than the PSR of any segment not searched 
that period. However, there may be many important operational 
considerations leading to selection of an allocation yielding somewhat less 
POS than is theoretically possible: the mathematics is only a guide!
Check the after-search PSR values to determine if a higher POS might be 
achievable.
• If the after-search PSR of a segment searched is lower than for a 
segment not searched, it is being “over-searched” at the expense of 
expanding into new segments.
• Consider reallocating some searchers from segments with the 
lowest after-search PSR into additional segments.
Check and 
Adjust for 
