POS)

Inland SAR Planning Student Guide
174 30 October 2014
Optimal Allocation 
• If the after-search PSR of the segments searched are not relatively 
equal to each other, some segments are being over-searched while 
others are being under-searched.
• Consider reallocating some searchers from segments with the 
lowest after-search PSR into segments with the highest aftersearch PSR.
• If the after-search PSR of a segment searched is still higher than 
for the pre-search PSR of another segment searched, the second 
segment is being over-searched at the other’s expense.
• It is possible too many segments are being attempted. 
Consider reallocating the searchers from the lower segment 
into the higher.
