Optimal Allocation
An alternative to the PSR Based Ground Effort Allocation worksheet is to 
write a computer program that uses the algorithm (computational 
procedure) originally developed by Charnes and Cooper, enter the 
required information (total available effort, W, V, POC and Area for each 
segment) and allow the computer to perform the necessary computations 
to calculate the amount of effort that should be placed in each segment. 
This relieves the planner of the need to go through the “trial and error” or 
“successive approximations” method described above.
As a class, complete the “Ground Effort Allocation Exercise” from the 
Practice Labs section of this student guide again, this time using the 
provided computer program to demonstrate the ease of determining an 
optimal allocation and experimenting with search effort allocations.
