Cumulative POD
PODcum demonstrates to the search planner how well an individual 
segment has been searched over time; the cumulative likelihood the 
searchers would have detected the search object if it had been in the 
segment and able to be found. PODcum demonstrates a “decreasing rate of 
return”: PODcum increases with each successive search, but at a decreasing 
rate.
A search is conducted in a segment with a search effort of POD=30% for 
10 search periods. PODcum increases toward 100%; however, PODcum
increases at a lesser amount with each successive search.
