195 30 October 2012
AIR EFFORT ALLOCATION LABS
Complete Air Effort Allocation Worksheets for the search problems 
below. All of the information you will need is given. Investigate the 
POC-POD-POS options and other search considerations. Use the “All 
Flight Types” ASAD Probability Chart and the “Probability Along 
Track” value for 110% of route of flight.
A blank worksheet is provided for each problem. The “answers” are 
printed after each worksheet. Make certain to check your answers against 
the correct answer sheet – many look alike. Line-by-line instructions for 
the worksheets can be found in the Student Guide, Appendix C. 
A light aircraft has been reported overdue from point “A” to point “B.” 
The length of this flight is 217 nm. There will be 6 hours of daylight 
remaining after SRUs arrival on-scene. Visibility along the route of flight 
is 6 nm and the terrain is flat with 10% vegetation. There are no 
jurisdictional boundaries. Aircraft cannot overfly their on-scene 
endurance limit (round down the number of full tracks). No observer 
limitations.
