196 30 October 2012
AIR EFFORT ALLOCATION LABS
A light aircraft has been reported overdue from point “A” to point “B.” 
The length of this flight is 100 nm. The aircraft’s flight takes it through 3 
areas of varying conditions as indicated below but you are unable to 
determine if the aircraft was IFR or VFR, so use the all flight types 
probability chart. No observer limitations.
Sub-area 1 (S1): There will be 7 hours of daylight remaining after SRU 
arrival on-scene. Visibility along the route of flight is 15 nm over rolling 
hills with moderate cover. Aircraft cannot overfly their on-scene 
endurance limit (round down the number of full tracks).
Sub-area 2 (S2): There will be 4.5 hours of daylight remaining after SRU 
arrival on-scene. Visibility along the route of flight is 3 nm at best and the 
terrain has 75% vegetation cover in this more mountainous area. Aircraft 
are authorized overfly their on-scene endurance limit.
Sub-area 3 (S3): There will be 5 hours of daylight remaining after SRU 
arrival on-scene. Visibility along the route of flight is 3 nm at best over 
open, rolling hills. Aircraft are authorized overfly their on-scene 
endurance limit.
