Begin Section B by placing an operationally valid number of searchers into as many of the highest PSR value segments as it 
seems reasonable to search during this operational period and calculate through Line 19 for those segments. Then, experiment 
(lines 13-19) with varying assignment and segment combinations to explore the effects on POS and post-search PSR. Consider 
selecting an assignment plan that is operationally valid and yields a POS relatively near the maximum.
Notes: - The Overall POS expected for this planning period equals the SUM of all Line 17 POS values for this period.
- The maximum POS occurs when the Line 19 PSR of all segments searched during this period are equal and are not less 
than that of the highest unsearched segment.
- On subsequent searches, use the most recently updated Line 18 (POC After This Search) for PSR calculations.

