Note we use the first, simpler formula 
when searching full tracks. We use the 
second, longer formula for wandering 
types of searches in which searchers are 
assigned a “time to search,” not a 
routing or number of tracks. The two 
should yield the same spacing for fulltrack searches in which the segment 
area = baseline x width.

