Ground Search Labs
You are searching for a missing hunter and have narrowed your search 
down to a search area of 4.78 sq miles. Region A has an area of 2.22 
square miles with a consensus POC of 60%. Region B has an area of 2.56 
square miles with a consensus POC of 40%. There are 7 hours of daylight 
remaining. You have segmented your two regions using natural 
boundaries. Sweep width in all segments was determined by a rain dance 
performed in the segments. You have 150 grid searchers to use during this 
search period. 
SEARCH SEGMENT DATA
Segment Length Base Sweep Width
A1 1.70 mi 0.6 mi 40 ft
A2 1.50 mi 0.3 mi 50 ft
A3 1.50 mi 0.5 mi 60 ft
B1 2.10 mi 0.8 mi 100 ft
B2 1.75 mi 0.5 mi 80 ft
After working the problem with the given 150 searchers, determine how 
you would change your plan if only 50 searchers showed up. Would you 
allocate you searchers in the mathematically optimal way? Why/why not?
You are searching for an overdue hiker and have narrowed your search 
down to a 7.10 sq mile area that you have sub-divided into 3 regions. 
Region A has an area of 2.7 square miles with a POC of 50%. Region B: 
1.44 square miles with 20% POC, and Region C: 2.96 square miles with 
30% POC. There are 6 hours of daylight remaining. You have segmented 
your regions and “rain danced” your sweep widths as indicated below. 
You have only 75 grid searchers available! 
SEARCH SEGMENT DATA
Segment Length Base Sweep Width
A1 1.5 mi 0.7 mi 35 ft
